<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.2618055>
    dc:description "FIGURE 9. Breeding habitat of Microhyla aurantiventris sp. nov. at the type locality in Tram Lap forest, Gia Lai Province; note the dead trees due to construction of a new road across the forest." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/2618055/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.2618045>
    dc:description "FIGURE 4. Dorsal (A), ventral (B), and dorso-lateral (C) views of male holotype of Microhyla aurantiventris. sp. nov. in preservative. Scale bar equals to 5 mm. Photos by L.T. Nguyen." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/2618045/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.2618047>
    dc:description "FIGURE 5. Male holotype of Microhyla aurantiventris sp. nov. in life. A, dorso-lateral view; B, dorsal view; C, ventral view; D, palmar view of left hand; E, thenar view of left foot; and F, iris coloration. (Note: the semicircle seen in the eye of frog in F is from a ring flash and not a natural coloration). Photos by L.T. Nguyen." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/2618047/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.2618049>
    dc:description "FIGURE 6. Dorsal and ventral views of paratypes of Microhyla aurantiventris sp. nov. in life showing variation in dorsal coloration pattern and coloration of ventral surface and throat of males and a single female (from left to right, top down, same for both upper and lower parts): males ITBCZ 4362–4369, ITBCZ 4371, and female ITBCZ 4360. Scale bar is 0.5 cm. Photos by L.T. Nguyen." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/2618049/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.2618051>
    dc:description "FIGURE 7. Advertisement call of Microhyla aurantiventris sp. nov. (paratype ITBCZ 4506). A, 12 s waveform of relative amplitude (oscillogram, Rel. amp.) of a call series; B, an expanded 0.5 s waveform of one call containing 18 pulses per cal; C, corresponding spectrogram of the same call; D, power spectrum (relative amplitude vs. frequency) of a single call depicted in B (521 FFT points, Hanning window)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/2618051/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.2618057>
    dc:description "FIGURE 10. The four sympatric species of Microhyla recorded at the type locality of Microhyla aurantriventris sp. nov. (Vietnam, Gia Lai Province, Tram Lap Forest). A, M. butleri; B, M. heymonsi; C, M. mukhlesuri; and D, M. pulverata." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/2618057/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.2618039>
    dc:description "FIGURE 1. Type locality (red dot) of Microhyla aurantiventris sp. nov. in Gia Lai Province, Vietnam." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/2618039/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.2618043>
    dc:description "FIGURE 3. Bayesian inference tree for the Microhyla butleri species group derived from analyses of 16S rRNA gene fragment. Symbols at the internal nodes are Bayesian posterior probabilities and bootstrap proportions from BI and ML, respectively: asterisk: supported 100% by BI, and ML; plus sign: supported 95–99% by BI and 70–99% by ML; hyphen: unsupported. Sequences of M. heymonsi, M. berdmorei, and Rhacophorus schlegelii are used as outgroups. Sympatric populations of M. aurantiventris sp. nov. and M. butleri in Tram Lap, Gia Lai underlined. Malaysian sample of M. butleri corresponds to the type locality of this species. Thumbnails show males of Microhyla aurantiventris sp. nov. (photo by L.T. Nguyen) and M. butleri s. str. (photo by N.A. Poyarkov) from respective type localities." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/2618043/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.2618053>
    dc:description "FIGURE 8. Advertisement call of Microhyla butleri collected from the same locality as the new species (Tram Lap, Gia Lai Province; ITBCZ 4376). A, 12 s waveform of relative amplitude (oscillogram, Rel. amp.) of a call series; B, an expanded 0.5 s waveform of single call containing 35 pulses; C, corresponding spectrogram of the same call; D, power spectrum (relative amplitude vs. frequency) of a single call depicted in B (512 FFT points, Hanning window)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/2618053/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

